    <section class="pt-20 md:pt-36 px-6">
      <div class="title flex-col items-center space-y-4 pb-4 border-b-2">
        <p class="text-base font-bold text-secondary">Bitology Education</p>
        <p class="font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl">Let's Begin Bitcoin</p>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section
      class="note flex-col space-y-4 text-xl md:text-2xl p-4 md:px-8 md:w-[90%]"
    >
      <p>
        Welcome to the world of Bitcoin! Whether you're a curious newcomer or
        someone looking to dive deeper into this revolutionary technology, this
        guide will help you understand the basics and get started with Bitcoin.
      </p>
      <!-- <img src="/images/tarp-czee.png" class="w-60 mx-auto" alt="tarp-czee"> -->

      <p class="font-bold">What Is BITCOIN?</p>

      <p>
        Bitcoin is a type of digital currency, created and held electronically.
        It was invented in 2008 by an unknown person or group of people using
        the name Satoshi Nakamoto. Unlike traditional currencies, Bitcoin is
        decentralized, meaning no central authority or government controls it.
      </p>

      <img src="/images/btcdog.png" alt="crypto-scammers" />
      <p>
        As among all cryptocurrencies, <span class="font-bold">Bitcoin </span>is
        the first ever cryptocurrency existing introducing a very swift way of
        decentralized currency.
      </p>

      <p class="font-bold">How Does Bitcoin Work?</p>

      <p class="font-bold text-lg">Blockchain Technology</p>

      <p>
        At its core, Bitcoin operates on a technology called blockchain. This is
        a public ledger that records all Bitcoin transactions. Each block in the
        chain contains a list of transactions, and once a block is filled, it's
        added to the chain in a linear, chronological order.
      </p>

      <p class="font-bold text-lg">Mining</p>

      <p>
        New Bitcoins are created through a process called mining. Miners use
        powerful computers to solve complex mathematical problems. When they
        solve these problems, they verify transactions and add them to the
        blockchain, earning new Bitcoins as a reward.
      </p>

      <p class="font-bold text-lg">Transactions</p>

      <p>
        Sending Bitcoin is as simple as sending an email. Each user has a unique
        address, and transactions are verified by the network of miners,
        ensuring they are secure and irreversible.
      </p>

      <p class="font-bold">Getting started with Bitcoin</p>

      <p>
        To start using Bitcoin, you'll need a digital wallet where you can store
        your Bitcoins. There are several types of wallets available, including
        mobile, desktop, hardware, and online wallets. Each type has its own set
        of features, so choose one that best fits your needs and level of
        security.
      </p>

      <p>
        Once you have a wallet, the next step is to buy Bitcoin. You can
        purchase Bitcoin from cryptocurrency exchanges, which allow you to trade
        traditional currency for Bitcoin. Popular exchanges include Coinbase,
        Binance, and Kraken. These platforms are user-friendly and provide a
        secure way to buy and sell Bitcoin.
      </p>

      <p>
        Securing your Bitcoin is crucial. Make sure to keep your wallet safe by
        using strong passwords and enabling two-factor authentication. For added
        security, you might want to consider using a hardware wallet, which
        stores your Bitcoin offline and is less vulnerable to hacking.
      </p>

      <p>
        After you've acquired Bitcoin and secured it, you can start using it for
        various purposes. Bitcoin can be used to make purchases from merchants
        that accept it, both online and offline. Additionally, you can invest in
        Bitcoin or transfer money internationally with ease and lower fees
        compared to traditional methods. The growing acceptance of Bitcoin means
        you have more opportunities to use it in your daily life.
      </p>

      <p class="summary-tag font-bold underline">Summary</p>
      <p class="summary-head font-semibold">What Is Bitcoin?</p>
      <p>
        Bitcoin is a groundbreaking technology with the potential to transform
        the financial landscape. By understanding its basics and taking the
        right steps to get started, you can join the growing community of
        Bitcoin users and explore the opportunities it offers. Welcome to the
        future of money!
      </p>
    </section>
